 </div> 
</div> 
<p><strong>Scarlet Aeonia</strong> is an&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Incantations" href="/Incantations" target="">Incantation</a>&nbsp;in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. <strong>Scarlet Aeonia spell</strong>&nbsp;creates a giant flower that explodes with scarlet rot.&nbsp;Updated to&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Patch Notes" href="/Patch+Notes">Patch 1.07</a>.</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>Technique of Malenia, the Goddess of Rot.<br></em><br><em>Creates a gigantic flower that blooms into an explosion of scarlet</em>&nbsp;<em>rot.</em><br><em><br>Each time the scarlet flower blooms, Malenia's rot advances. It has</em>&nbsp;<em>bloomed twice already. With the third bloom, she will become a</em>&nbsp;t<em>rue goddess.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to find Scarlet Aeonia</h3> 
<p>Where to find <strong>Scarlet Aeonia</strong>:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Trade <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Remembrance of the Rot Goddess" href="/Remembrance+of+the+Rot+Goddess">Remembrance of the Rot Goddess</a> with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Enia" href="/Enia" target="">Enia</a> at <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Roundtable Hold" href="/Roundtable+Hold" target="">Roundtable Hold</a>.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring&nbsp;Scarlet Aeonia Guide</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li><a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Servants of Rot Incantations" href="/Servants+of+Rot+Incantations" target="">Servants of Rot Incantation</a></li> 
 <li>Stamina Cost:&nbsp;50</li> 
 <li>Deals physical and slightly magic damage</li> 
 <li>Inflicts Scarlet Rot on opponents. Buildup is 150 on initial explosion and 50 per tick in lingering area of effect</li> 
 <li><span style="color: #ff9900;">Note:</span>&nbsp;Multiple buffs in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Patch Notes" href="/Patch+Notes">Patch 1.07</a> - FP cost reduced from 56 to 48, attack power increased and poise damage and stamina damage to guarding enemies both increased. The range of the attack on landing was increased and recovery time increased. Poise during activation was also increased. Interestingly, although not stated in the patch notes, the stamina cost for this spell was also decreased, from 66 to 50.</li> 
</ul> 
